00:04:14.510 --> 00:04:16.510
Fall through the modern miracle of colorization.

00:04:16.510 --> 00:04:21.840
Here I am.

00:04:21.840 --> 00:04:24.840
Of course this colorization technique isn't always totally accurate.

00:04:24.840 --> 00:04:28.240
There.

00:04:28.240 --> 00:04:29.240
That's better.

00:04:29.240 --> 00:04:32.240
At least it's one way to make something old look like something new.

00:04:32.240 --> 00:04:37.810
And that's exactly what I have to do for Mr. Batenback's history class.

00:04:37.810 --> 00:04:40.810
Take something old, tired, and worn out, and reinvent it.

00:04:40.810 --> 00:04:43.810
Well, you can't get more worn out than these sneakers.

00:04:43.810 --> 00:04:46.810
But with a little help from Dad's trusty magic markers?

00:04:47.810 --> 00:04:48.810
Good as new.

00:04:48.810 --> 00:04:49.810
Only better.

00:04:49.810 --> 00:04:51.810
And what about these jeans?

00:04:51.810 --> 00:04:53.810
You've seen them once, you've seen them a thousand times,

00:04:53.810 --> 00:04:55.810
but by just roughing them up.

00:04:57.810 --> 00:04:59.810
Now new jeans look like old jeans,

00:04:59.810 --> 00:05:01.810
which makes them even newer jeans.

00:05:01.810 --> 00:05:02.810
It's a whole new concept.

00:05:02.810 --> 00:05:05.810
I guess it's just a matter of looking at an old thing in a new light.

00:05:06.810 --> 00:05:08.810
Sis, can I borrow five bucks?

00:05:08.810 --> 00:05:09.810
I had asked...

00:05:09.810 --> 00:05:11.810
I wanted to do you the favor of helping you

00:05:11.810 --> 00:05:13.810
establish credit with the future financial giant.

00:05:13.810 --> 00:05:16.810
